<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Containing WH — Question Word Digraph for Scrabble</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">WH is the "question word" digraph — WHO, WHAT, WHERE, WHEN, WHY all start with it. In Scrabble, W(4) + H(4) gives an impressive 8-point base value, the highest of any common digraph. When you hold W and H together, you have a premium scoring combination that demands to be played.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why WH Is Premium</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">W(4) + H(4) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">150+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid WH words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Start</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Almost always WH-</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>WH has the highest base digraph value of any common pair — 8 points before other tiles are counted. WHACK alone scores 17 points from just 5 tiles. The trade-off is that WH words nearly always start with WH-, limiting positional flexibility.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring WH Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
