<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for WH Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play W on premium squares:</span> W is worth 4 points. On a DLS it's 8, on a TLS it's 12. Since WH words start with W, target row/column starts that align W with premiums.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WH words are opening plays:</span> WHACK, WHALE, WHEAT are excellent first moves — they cover the centre star and extend 5-6 tiles toward edge premiums.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't hold W+H too long:</span> With only 2 W tiles and 2 H tiles in the bag, these are semi-rare. Play WH words when they score 12+ rather than waiting for the perfect moment.</p>
  </div>
</div>

